just don't want to be the one to take the heat for turning the server FFA.<br><br>Either way, there are a lot of people doing what they can to make this work.  Your sitting on the sidelines declaring the calendar dead every other day is not doing anything constructive.<br><br>If you Truly Believe(tm) that the calendar is dead, then go do what you want.  Have your guild go do what you want.  But I know and you know that the calendar system isn't dead.<br><br>Why else would you keep calling for its destruction?  If it was dead, nobody would respect the calendar, and you could safely FFA to your heart's content.  But ... apparently it isn't.<br><br>Maybe this little story (with names removed) will warm your heart a bit.  Who knows.  It's the story of a tiny guild with maybe 4 people in it who are planes capable.  A guild with no real ties to any of the uber guilds.  A guild with no way to really do any raids at all on their own.<br><br>A member of this guild got a chance to go to a plane, and went.  they had fun.  The next day, someone from another guild that was significantly larger and able to mount raids contacted them.  The offer was made to take the little guild on many planes runs, if the little guild would act as a front organization for posting rights on the calendar.<br><br>The little guild declined.  At the risk of potentially losing their one known invitation to planes/dragons/other raids.  And you know why they declined?<br><br>BECAUSE THEY BELIEVED IN THE CALENDAR.<br><br>If someone who has that much to lose can stand behind this calendar, I hope you will decide to work to fix the system, instead of trying to tear it down.<br><br>Bias Schmias<br>48th Warrior<br>Glossolalia<br><br>Disclaimer:  I am not accusing you or anyone from your guild of trying to be 'uber-uber' or 'ruin the server'.  So let's not go down that path everyone, ok?  I don't think that's what is going on, and it's not helpful to point fingers and play the blame game.