olor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubiasschmias.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bias Schmias</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Toede</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/13/00 1:43:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Questions =)</span><hr size=1> Aegirson:<br><br>So you are saying that, regardless of anything anyone does from this point forward, you are going to be disgregarding the calendar?<br><br>Speak plainly on this issue.  I'm a &quot;noob&quot; in this, and I need you to be clear in your motivations.<br><br>If you speak for all of Clan Icewind, I would greatly appreciate it if you could answer the following questions, just so that everyone can be clear on what you are saying, and we can move on from here.<br><br>* Do you intend to respect the calendar after today?<br>* If you are approached by representatives of a new calendaring system after today, will you accept their decision, even if you have no part in making that decision?<br><br>I point you back to my post previous to this one.  If you intend to go FFA, then do it.  Do not try to make everyone else agree with you so you can feel better about deciding to go FFA.<br><br>If you and your guild are going to cease respecting the calendar, speak plainly.  If you are going to continue respecting the calendar, please help us to get a calendar system in place.<br><br>To be blunt: either take the reputation hit for being the guild that kills the calendar and move on, knowing you made the right decision, or help to make the calendar more usable by all, and know that you made the right decision.<br><br>To have the amount of influence you have and not commit to one path or the other and work towards that end openly and honestly is a waste.<br><br>Bias Schmias<br>48th Warrior<br>Glossolalia <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowra