scape.&quot;<br><br>As usual, bonus points for naming the film.<br><br>Bias Schmias<br>48th Warrior<br>Glossolalia <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukinakalliope.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kina Kalliope</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.nwlink.com/~jshih/blunoteCLR.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Toede</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/13/00 2:42:31 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Big Brother rule</span><hr size=1> I did not see that the Big Brother rule had gone into effect already (thought it was still in discussion) or I would have certainly followed the guidelines.  Also, I was told that Inny was not up on Saturday and the Maestro spawned about the same time we decided to call it a night and were porting out.  My apologies if I was misinformed.<br><br>Kina Kalliope, Guild Leader<br>Eternal Valor <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukaras.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Karas</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Toede</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/13/00 2:45:26 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.netcarrier.com/~traney/images/ranger.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Cripes...</span><hr size=1> Um...correction Qwai. <br><br><br>Gms DO support player made agreements....a calendar is a player made agreement.  <br><br><br>And besides...from my understanding the split is going to be soon, and there will be many leaving I understand. For those leaving, I would be suprised to see them even bother worrying about the calendar if they are going...<br><br><br>For those staying, the calendar still stands....if 2-3 big guilds go...it doesnt nullify the fact that many others still support the calendar.<br><br> <p>Karas LightStrider<BR>Guild Master<BR>Champions of Norrath<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uaegirson.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aegirson</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.nagafen.com/images/characters/aegsmall.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Toede Master</span><br>  Posts: 156<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/13/00 2:46:04 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.eqraid.org/images/characters/aeg.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: enough already</span><hr size=1> Well it's kinda funny you know. I've been hosting the calendar and administering it (yes I still get tells today to allow access and so forth) for close to a year now, and I'm being called part of the problem. <br><br>On the other side, I have to applaud the work and Rewena and Edwina - and the others that have actively tried to support the calendar in the recent weeks. I hope they know what they are getting themselves into <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Unfortunately I wished that help came when I asked for it 6+ months ago. It's only after truely threatening FFA that people are coming out of the woods and taking this stuff semi seriously.<br><br>I seriously doubt I have any more influence exept as an officer of CIW. Besides, isn't it a little moronic to ask me to use my &quot;influence&quot; to suit your needs or STFU? There is a problem, and from our standpoint, there are several solutions - not just one. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umikjowynterwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MikJo Wynterwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Toede</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/13/00 2:58:37 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/mtgclassic/seph9.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: enough already</span><hr size=1> Let me explain what happened yesterday.<br><br>Crimson Coalition and Spirits of fyre were in hate (CFA)<br>The whole raid was fubared from the get go, but thats my fault. anyways, when it came time to do Meastro then Inny, a lot fo peepz decided it was to late and left. There were 18 of us left.  Despite numerous suggestions to call in a  big brother guild, many wanted to finish clearing. Evenutally almost everyone left, it was 4am, and everyone had to work today.<br><br>We didnt call in anyone, and yes thats my fault. So i apologize for that. i agree with the big brother system.<br>Shoot me.<br><br>Stygar/Qwai, i respect you as a player, so dont take this personally, but everyone of your posts has to do with &quot;lets trash the calendar&quot; if you hate the calendar so much, offer a solution. Be part of the soluition, not the problem. <p><p>-------------------------------------------<br><font face="Times New Roman,Times"><font color="#000000">Mikjo Wynterwolf</font></font><br><font face="Times New Roman,Times"><font color="#000000">Wanderer ofthe 53rd Circle</font></font><br><font face="Times New Roman,Times"><font color="#000000">Spokesdruid of the Crimson Fyre Alliance<font></font><br><font face="Wingdings"><font color="#000000"><font size=-2>the unkemptshall rise again</font></font></font><br>-------------------------------------------</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udarkoak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DarkOak</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Toede</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/13/00 3:04:50 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   :)</span><hr size=1> If the noob leader of CIW can't see that their isn't an Epic calendar or even a rule at the moment for BB guilds, he's two sandwiches short of a picnic.<br><br>I even went and checked to see if there WAS anyone posted on the Epic Calendar. The only name on their was KEG, and that was for PoA.<br><br>How hard is it for you to do a /tell to person in Hate..<br>'Heya, how goes the raid?  Do you have enough for Innie/Maestro, and/or plan to kill them?'<br>&quot;No, we don't have enough for them.&quot;<br>'Ok. Are you almost done in Hate?'<br>&quot;Yeah we have about 20 minutes left.&quot;<br>'Ok cool.'<br><br>The alliance I'm in is not even listed in the BB bit, yet I usually like to find out if the current guild in the plane after the server just came back up was able to kill X God / mob, or will be able to.<br><br>For now, the onus of finding out is on you Stygar, and the other BB guilds/alliances, until everyone knows about and the majority agree to the current rules. Even after the finalization, etc a quick /tell to whoever's in X plane can usually yield a lot of information about how the raid is progressing.<br><br>If you don't like the small responsibility of finding out from X guild if they will be able to kill the 'boss' mobs of said plane, then perhaps the BB troupe isn't for you.<br><br>As for seeing to the deletion of the calendar? Maybe far off in the future it will need to be revised, possibly dismantled, but we aren't there yet.<br><br><br>Now onto Sirth and company. I spoke with Sirth and Rogfear a fair amount, and according to them, had received a login/password from Aegirson. They also claimed to have enough planeables to post a raid. Which I couldn't really fathom, until finding out they had somewhat of an alliance with Intrepid Spirit and possibly other guilds/organizations. Which gave them maybe 20 planeables tops. But they don't seem to want to post that they are allied with Guild Y and Z anywhere, which seems somewhat suspicious.<br>So, I'll ask you, who was in Sirth and company that went into Hate last night to try and grab Innie/Maestro from (obviously) CIW?<br>I wasn't there so I don't know who was in the Plane, were you there? Was a member of the previous nights guild there? Sirth and company did have Hate last Thursday night, perhaps they had camped out for whatever reason or only some did and the rest gated?<br><br>Right now the only thing we have is you receiving reports from ESP about Sirth and company 'sneaking' into Hate last night. They may very well have been there. What were there intentions? Did Sirth or Rogfear themselves say they were going to grab Innie/Maestro? Or was it an interpretation? They are in Hate! They must be going to kill Maestro/Inny.<br><br>Hmm. Anyways.<br><br>Regards,<br><br>Darin DarkOak<br>&quot;The above is my own, not my guilds stand/viewpoint.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubiasschmias.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bias Schmias</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Toede</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/13/00 3:28:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: part of the problem, redux</span><hr size=1> <br>Ok, last thing i'll say and then i'll try to not post much more in this thread if i can help it.<br><br>Aegirson:  by continuing to threaten FFA but not actually doing anything, you are part of the problem.  You are undermining the work that is being done RIGHT NOW to keep the calendar going.<br><br>I agree, it sucks you couldn't get help six months ago to keep the calendar running and make things better.  That bites.  6 months ago, I was a lowbie who didn't even know what the hell KEG was, except a thing you put beer in.<br><br>I want to thank you for taking on the thankless and unenviable task of trying to run the calendar system for as long as you have.  But do you really want to tear down what you've worked so hard to maintain?  I don't know you, or your guild, or anyone on this board in-game.  And yet, I think highly enough of your current &quot;broken&quot; calendaring system that I'm risking losing my one invitation i've gotten to a plane raid by standing up for it.<br><br>Isn't that worth preserving, Aegirson?  <br><br>All I am saying to you, to all of CIW, to BOTS, to KEG, to everyone who reads this messageboard:<br><br>State your intentions.<br><br>If you are going to go FFA because you are fed up with the calendar and you honestly don't believe it will work anymore, DO IT.<br><br>if you are just honestly sick of working on the calendar, but think it could work if someone else were to run it, and would support whatever decisions were made without your input, SAY THAT.<br><br>If you want to have a hand in making the calendar better and you aren't totally burnt out yet, DO THAT.<br><br>It is your (in my eyes) lack of commitment in either direction at this point that is what makes you &quot;part of the problem&quot;.<br><br>I hate that choice of words, because it turns this into an even more combative discussion than it already is.  ugh.<br><br>All I think anyone wants at this point from you, or from Stygar, or from anyone else who has been espousing FFA every time something goes wrong lately is for you to make a stand. <br><br>Make a stand, make it public, and live with your decision.  Even if your stand is to stop providing input into changes and enforcement of rules.  Even if you choose to plunge the server into FFA and (imho) chaos.<br><br>Pick a side, and start swinging.  Choose which one you truly believe in, and fight to the bitter end, or the triumphant conclusion.  Or both. Probably both, really.<br><br>Bias Schmias<br>48th Warrior<br>Glossolalia<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uedwinanytengayle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EdwinaNytengayle</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Toede Master</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/13/00 4:10:22 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/TimesSquare/Labyrinth/1868/Ed.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: part of the problem, redux</span><hr size=1> CIW has peeped up on the proposals...both on Bradan's and mine.  While they supported Bradan's, they nayed the other, but they have given no reasons for being against that proposal, nor suggestions on how to make it acceptable to them (least from what I have seen on this board).  Qwai, perhaps you'd care to give some input?<br><br>Aegirson, when you asked 6 or 8 months ago for assistance, I said that I would.  When you asked 2 months ago for assistance, I again offered mine.  You took on a world of shit to uphold the calendar set up almost a year ago, with very little support, and I applaud that effort, and have offered over the months to share that burden so that it was not quite so heavy.  But then, I am merely a name on a board in the ether, eh? <p><B><FONT FACE="Tahoma" COLOR="#ffffff">Edwina Nytengayle<BR><I>54<SUP>th</SUP> Cleric</B><BR></I></FONT><A HREF="http://www.geocities.com/TimesSquare/Labyrinth/1868"><I><FONT FACE="Tahoma" SIZE=2 COLOR="#ffffff">Knights of Phoenix</I></FONT></A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uankhorahil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ankhorahil</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://63.89.105.245/eq/skull9.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Toede</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/13/00 5:06:14 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: part of the problem, redux</span><hr size=1> Hello?! *thump thump* McFly?! *thump thump* Don't you remember you voted 'nay' on the proposal? And now you want a proposal that's not in effect yet, which you didn't agree with, to help you out? *thump thump*<br><br>You know, if you had taken all the time to propose alternate solutions instead of constantly saying &quot;this won't ever work&quot; then maybe we'd have come to a consensus by now, and gods wouldn't be staying up.<br><br>You insist on being the antagonist, and it's getting old, Qwai.<br><br>Ankh <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ustygar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stygar</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Toede</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/13/00 7:55:28 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.eqraid.org/images/characters/qwai.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: part of the problem, redux</span><hr size=1> There are 8-10 people from Keg, Bots, For, and CIW who spent 4-5 hours in a chat room trying to come up with a viable option. You guys shot it down. <br><br>40 peep minimum to post. (look at Rewenas list, this would free up ALOT of days on the calendar)<br><br>Extra posting days for Big brother guilds if available.<br>To qualify as a BB guild beat Isle 6 in sky. MFH just qualified as the 5th BB guild.<br><br>If your posting guild has any doubt about killing a god or quest mob ask the BB guild who is up next on list to come help within a reasonable hour.<br><br>No 2/3 rule. Max 6 guests from a guild.<br><br><br>Who cares who is moving, why should we waste the next month or so waiting on the split? The split may never happen after Vellious. Quit stalling, get this shit done, or lets FFA. <br><br>Qwai<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showMessageRange?topicID=2.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showMessageRange?topicID=2.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showMessageRange?topicID=2.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showMessageRange?topicID=2.topic&start=81&stop=91>5</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showPrevMessage?topicID=2.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showNextMessage?topicID=2.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.emailToFriend?topicID=2.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.threadControl?topicID=2.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/deleteThreadFire.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop rece